{
  "texts": [
    "Hence, the SHERPA \"importance score\" represent the contribution of each feature to the difference between the predicted probability and the expected probability given all the other features.",
    "The score thus depends on the units of the classification model's output.",
    "As these units are probabilities, SHERPA's output can be interpreted along the same line (Lundberg & Lee, 2017).",
    "The SHAP scale represents the magnitude and direction of the contribution of a feature, such as an ERP component, to the output of a machine learning model.",
    "For our SHERPA approach, we used absolute values, with zero representing a neutral contribution, meaning that the feature has no effect on the output of the model."
  ]
}